Well, horrible week has sort of come to an end. Both mentally & physically this week has been terrible for me. I really can't pin point any one thing that caused it...perhaps just a stress break down. I don't know. The weekend kinda helped me to put myself back together, but, finding out my car is worthless doesn't help.

So I just want to take this space here to formally apologize to anyone directly affected by my bad week. Ask me why it happened, I don't know why it happened...but it did. I think i'm together again...so, lets start over & forget the past week, k?

....and speaking of the car,,...if you would like to donate to get my car fixed, it would be greatly appreciated...........

g'night all

yea, its that time again. I'm home for Christmas break. As soon as I got in, I wanted to watch the blue jackets vs. teh devils. Wasn't on (GRRRRRRRR)but, hey, the jackets won anyway 4-2. So then mom was showing me things she got for em for christmas. I wanted a christmas gift NOW....so, i begged & told her 'i don't have any pants that really fit. they're alltoo big' so she decided to give me a pair of jeans she got me...a 22...so i put them on, and, well, WAY too big. she's like "um...shit. try these on' and she pulls out another pair of pants she got me for chrsitmas. also a 22. yeas, too big. she's like 'oh shit.' so i got happy & went to dad's and started trying on all my old dresses & stuff. yea, my HS graduation dress, fits me better now than it did then! i love this. hehe. she's like 'um, i think i'm gonn ahave to take you shopping before i buy anything else'

basically, all in all its been a good day. :) can't wait to see my friends. I need sleep. NIGHTY!


(oh! my media ethics paper....28/30....defenately an A!!!!!!!)

Krystal just told me some Duncan news: He's gone for good this time. He went UA and he's on his way back to Ireland.......to stay. 

Granted he treated me like crap, I still did have feelings for him to an extent. I felt ok knowing that he was in norfolk, and 8 hour drive away, and that he'd prolly come home with clayton again & I'd prolly get to see him.... Now that he's in Ireland for good now, I feel horrible....cause now the chance of working things out....is prolly not gonna happen. I wish I would have messaged him when I had the chance....

COLUMBUS BLUE JACKETS ACQUIRE RW TOMI KALLIO, D PAULI LEVOKARI FROM ATLANTA THRASHERS FOR RW CHRIS NIELSEN, D PETTERI NUMMELIN


yea, i'm so upset about that, and that's not all. The jackets are totally fucked. With neilsen gone, they just screwed syracuse....and nummelin was good to. SO, now that syracuse is screwed: check this out. Jean Luc Grand-Pierre is on the injured reserve, so who did they call up: Westcott. *eye roll* Let me tell ya how this is gonna work: IT WON'T !!!
Columbus is screwed, Syracuse is screwed, and with Syracuse being screwed, they prolly call up a bomber or 2, so depending on who they call up, THEY'LL be fucked over too. 

the next thing that actually scares me is that Espen Knutsen is being sent to surgery, and they don't even know what's wrong with him! Its somethign with his lower abdominal area, so, hopefully its nothign so bad he won't skate again.....then, we'd be fucked.

Anyway, I'm done bitching for now. I just realized, the Blue Jackets don't rank high, not because of the players have no talent, but because Doug Maclean & his crew can't make good decisions.....

I know, if you're familiar with other 'from home' posts, they're all un-happy & all that. Not this time. I've had a pretty good stay so far at home. Every night here (so far anyway) has been spent at mom's new house. I spend a lot of time here. Wednesday I helped mom work the kitchen at bingo, and had choir practice. Went to thanksgiving mass...saw Joey. As an old UD student, we chatted & all that. Joe's awsome! Then dinner was at the Downard residence. It was great times. That night: adam c. (now neighbor) and james, 2 of my friends/classmates came over to fix mom's sink, brought the beers...but couldn't do it, so we chilled & drank. then we found out there was a party at Dustin's! so, we called & had chanda come in & get us. hehe. Went out there & saw people I graduated with that I haven't seen in a long time. I miss them all, and it was funny, cause I've never been drunk around them. LOL! Awsome. Wade was out there... interesting to say the least *angel face on* anyway....we chilled & i acme back to the house. me, chanda & wade chilled for a little. wade went home, i passed out, and chanda went to work. poor girl. Friday: party at chanda's I didn't go out till like 1:30, but sara & wade were still there (and obviously chanda) we chilled & watched some late  night HBO & the MAX...0:) ya know. then wade & i left. sara was staying there. SO, here I am typing.Spent time with Krystal today too.  Also earlier today, I spent  like 3 hours at the PDQ talking to ryan. I love talking to him. He's so awsome. I still love him. and he knows this, but, I just know nothing will come of it. Him & I are gonna have a long talk when I'm home for christmas, just me & him. somewhere otehr than the PDQ, and nobody else around. It'll be fun. Hopefully get some things out in the open...everything about a year ago, and well, just stuff. I can't wait.
N-E-way......I'm going to go to bed. Nighty!!!!

Lots of stuff has happened since the last update. I'm beginning to get into that stress mode. Friday was the last friday PoD rehersal for the year. Always fun. ANd saturday was the last game.  As much as i like PoD and the people in it, I was glad to see the season come to an end. Friday & Saturday was also opera workshop weekend. Friday night I sang int he chorus, and afterwards went to see Abandon with Brian, his 2 friends from Erie & Katie. It was an Ok movie, but, eh..don't spend too much on it. Saturday: mom came for the game. She was supposed to cook for me, but instead her, my sister & katie made an executive decision to order pizza from dominos.....gee, thanks for asking guys.  I went to see the Opera Workshop too. It was really good. Now, to write a paper on it. Saturday night there was a party at Traci's so, of course, like a good girl, I went. Always fun times. :) Came home in the rain & passed out. Didn't get up for noon mass (sorry brian!) but, all was good.
10 PM mass was good. interesting homily. And, well, Brian hates me now...LOL! oops. I should keep my mouth shut.
Tonight, I went to classes...Swing Band was really a release. Sat around, and then did PoD group &  section pics. 
Came home & started to do MORE work... and then went to a Diversity Dinner. It was really fun, and interesting. Met some interesting people. I'm really glad I went. 

Also, all day sunday, I CLEANED MY ROOM! most of it anyway. I did pretty well. I just have some little things I have to deal with. But, the big pile is gone. BE PROUD!

But now, it's time for more work

FUN: tonight was the pledge recital, and I did a duet with my little. she kicked major ass, brandon (our accomp.) kicked ass,.me on the other hand didn't kick so much ass, but I wasn't important. my little was the one who was important. then afterwards my little treated me to dinner at Panera. It was great fun! we just got to sit & talk. went home, changed & then went to her room for b-day cake (HAPPY B-DAY CHRIS!!) then i went to my friend michelle's room in marycrest. always great fun...bitching about boys, plotting to get boys. things like that. always fun :-D LOVE YOU MICHELLE!

randomness:
random #1: i was talking to anne marquett today on campus, and this girl (who turned out being from my EDT class last year) just came up to me & told me i really look good after changing my hair & stuff. i look really nice apperently. It was totally random, but I do appreciate the fact that SOMEONE is paying attention. 

random #2: i walk into reichard for the pledge recital, and marabeth (spelling?) is standing there watching jane & michelle K. making up a flyerette routine, and she's like 'wow, you've got that groove down on the field. attitude & everything!' wow. LOL! that was jsut like...um...."i try. thanks" i keep tellin her i'm doing the flyerette clinics in april. she thinks i'm jsut teasin her when i do the dance like that & play with poms. WATCH ME ! no trying out though, i love my trumpet too much. 

Random #3: after pledege recital, i turn the corner after putting my horn away, and there stans saunders. definately didn't expect to see him there.......and the fact that he remembered that i am gonna have a party in early next semester for my b-day. totally odd.....

random #4: as i was leaving michelle's room tongiht, I go out the side door, ind out of the trash can jumps a raccoon. I hate those things. It was a huge fucker too...needless to say, i went the OPPOSITE direction of the dark side, the OPPOSITE directoon that that raccoon was standing and walked the long way. I hate those things. they steal marshmallows, and bite people. GO TO HELL RACCOON !!! DIE DIE DIE !!!

anyway, I'm off to bed. I need to dream of someone, and how to get them more in my life. NIGHTY!

things wern't TOOOOOOO bad. i was suposed to go to the caves on saturday, but was feeling horrible & fell asleep when i was supposed to be at the house meeting the guys to leave. Sorry fellas & sisters.....ended up going to Brooks' apartmetn, and ...yea...was defninately drunk by 11:30....
i called chris' house, and got yelled at by his mom.....i was so trashed. I did noon mass sunday AM...still drunk. EHS concert...still drunk...i started to come back down at like 6-ish in the evening. i was STILL hung over for 10 pm mass. what an interesting interesting feeling. the priest in his homoly said somethign about having too much to drink. Katie looks at me & grins realy big, then i look at Brian & he mouths 'sound familiar?!?!?!' and then afte mass i found out kevin was gonna say something, but just laughed instead. sheeeesh.
afeter mass, i practiced with my little for the pledge recital tomorrow.....(later t oday technically) and we so kick ass. I LOVE MY LITTLE!!!!!!!!!
come home....and i wantd to go to bed, but i had an awsome conversation with chris instead. I love talking to chris. 


anyway, it is bedtime now, so i'm out! nighty!

ok, so this doesn't cover the WHOLE weekend, just thursday to now, but, still most of the weekend. Thursday was a fun day. Comm went well, CU went ok. But the real fun began that night when we were singing tuck-ins. Yea, I was in Greg Kohls' bedroom *grin* Yea, it was awsome. there's no words to put here....LOL!But another fun tuck-in was Nate's. We tracked him down at the field house & sang to him. It was funny. Who would ever think of that? 
after tuck-ins i practiced with my wittle :D  I WUV MY WITTLE!!!!!! We're doing a clarinet duet (I'm playing trumpet obviously) for the pledge recital. It'll be great fun. The duet is kinda hard, but we kicked ass on it. It's not perfect, but hey, what can you expect from 2 people practicing together for the fist time without looking at it first? 

Friday was a yuck day weather wise, but event wise...awsome. I went to Fri @ 1 because I told Brian I'd be there to come hear his German song. He did well...and philosophy ended up being cancelled anyway! so YAY! After that was swing band run through of the concert....then PoD pictures. I can't wait to see those. They'll be fun, especially the buddy pics I got. I got one with my wittle (again, i WUV my wittle) adnt ehn I got one with michelle & ally, my 2 flyerette friends. they each had a trumpet, and I held Poms. after pics were all said & done.......some food...then it was Jazz concert time. the concert went awsome. I presonally flubbed, but who doesn't ya know? I can't wait to hear the recordign. I know it was TYTE! The jazz ensamble....always Tyte....so, yea. Concert done, tear down & then my mom, my dad, dorothy & pam (family friends from home), me & katie all went to Marions for pizza. It was yummy. I had my beer, had my pizza. had my salad. I was a happy camper (not to mention very full) Came home, and Katie & I watched CLUE & SPACEBALLS and had a mixed drink each. It was a good night. Couldn't ask for it to be any better. 

This AM (well afternoon) Katie & I went to marycrest for breakfast jsut like the olden days. :) I miss the olden days...but I LOVE living in a house. (and I didn't get up till 1 today!!!) 

anyway, I'm out. time to chill in the room i have to myself, or chill with kaite....who knows. prolly watch spaceballs again> LOL!

Well, it started out ok. My cousin Brandi got here at like 8 or so and brought me ski & came for a quick visit, which was all cool. It was her b-day today. I gave her a pinwheel, and I've never seen someone so amused. LOL!

So, after I walked with her & her guy back to the truck, I went to my friend Becky's for a little party because it was her birthday too!!! After a while, I got thinking that I didn't have my keys, so I called over to my house, and asked if the doors would be unlocked. They said they should be and I said ok.  I dind't think anymore about it, and I chilled more at becky's. When I was ready to go home, I came over, and both doors were locked. GRR! SO I go back over to Becky's (which is right across the parking lot) and I call back over here. Nobody answered. I kept callign & calling....no answer. So, I was getting mad. A guy that was at Becky's, Kevin, was trying to get me to go out with them to a club, but I told him I couldn't get into the house anyway. I didn't have money, and I look like crap. He still wanted me to go. I said I should go home, but I can't get in. I eventually asked him if he'd help me break into my house, cause I know we have an open window. So he said yea, and he took out the screen, climbed in the window, and unlocekd the door for me. He's awsome. We chatted for anotehr couple minutes, and he gave me his SN, told me he MIGHT be on some, but, not very often. ANd he said he likes it here & might come down for my 21st. So, killer!

Anyway, I'min the house & ready for bed....I get to my room upstairs & the door is locked. So, i stood there banging on the doro for a few mintues until finally my roommate's boyfriend finally let me in. I'm so mad. this is the 3rd time this has happened this year. I mean about the room, not the house. Anyway, I just needed to vent. I'm going to bed, because I need to get up in the AM & get to reichard by like 8am. So, good night.....

Oh, and Kevin is still a great guy....hehe. That's the best part fo the night. LOL!

I'll never forget this day, last year, or years to come. 


Lord, make me a channel of your peace.....
